Case 170 is an imported case involving a 56 year-old female Indonesian national who had arrived in Singapore on 9 March. She is warded in an isolation room at Singapore General Hospital (SGH). She is a family member of Case 152.

ï»¿She reported onset of symptoms on 6 March while in Indonesia, and presented at SGH on 9 March after arrival in Singapore. Subsequent test results confirmed COVID-19 infection on 10 March afternoon.
